.SH 19. ACCESSIBLE PDFS WITH PDF/UA
\f[B]cpdf \-print\-struct\-tree in.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Print a PDF\(cqs structure tree to standard output for inspection.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-extract\-struct\-tree in.pdf \-o out.json\f[R]
.PP
Extract the whole structure tree in JSON format.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for details.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-replace\-struct\-tree in.json in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Replace a PDF\(cqs structure tree with one from a JSON file.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-struct\-tree in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove the structure tree from a file.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-mark\-as\-artifact in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Mark all the content of the file as being an artifact.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-verify \(lqPDF/UA\-1(matterhorn)\(rq\f[R] \f[B]in.pdf\f[R]
[\-verify\-single <test>] [\-json]
.PP
Verify conformance with PDF/UA\-1.
.TP
\f[B]\-json\f[R]
Output conformance failures in JSON rather than plain text format.
.TP
\f[B]\-verify\-single\f[R] <test>
Verify just one test.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for list of tests.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-mark\-as [\(lqPDF/UA\-1\(rq | \(lqPDF/UA\-2\(rq] in.pdf \-o
out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Mark a PDF as conforming to PDF/UA\-1 or PDF/UA\-2
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-mark [\(lqPDF/UA\-1\(rq | \(lqPDF/UA\-2\(rq] in.pdf
\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove conformance marker from a PDF.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-create\-pdf\-ua\-<1 | 2> <string>\f[R] [\-create\-pdf\-pages
<n>] [\-create\-pdf\-papersize <papersize>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Create a new, blank, PDF/UA\-1 or PDF/UA\-2 file with the given title.
.TP
\f[B]\-create\-pdf\-pages\f[R] <n>
Give the number of pages.
.TP
\f[B]\-create\-pdf\-papersize\f[R] <papersize>
Give the paper size, e.g \(lqa3landscape\(rq or \(lq200pt 600pt\(rq
.SH 20. MISCELLANEOUS
\f[B]cpdf \-draft\f[R] \f[B]in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] [\-boxes]
[\-draft\-remove\-only <n>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove bit\-mapped (photographic) images from a PDF.
.TP
\f[B]\-boxes\f[R]
Replace each image with a crossed box to show where it was.
.TP
\f[B]\-draft\-remove\-only\f[R]
Remove only one image, with the given name.
The name can be obtained from, for example,
\f[B]\-list\-images\-used\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-all\-text in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o
out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove all text from a PDF.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-blacktext in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Make all text black.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-blacklines in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Make all lines black.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-blackfills in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Make all fills black.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-thinlines <min thickness> in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o
out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Make each line a minimum thickness.
A negative value will instead thin lines to the absolute of the value
given.
By processing twice, with a positive then negative figure, it is
therefore possible to clamp thicknesses to a range or single value.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-clean in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Deprecated.
This work is now done by default upon writing any file.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-set\-version <version number> in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Set the version of a PDF.
E.g for version 1.4, use \f[B]\-set\-version 4\f[R].
For PDF versions starting with 2, add ten to the number.
E.g for PDF 2.0, use \f[B]\-set\-version 10\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-copy\-id\-from source.pdf in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Copy the ID from one PDF to another.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-id in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove the ID from a PDF.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-list\-spot\-colors in.pdf\f[R]
.PP
List the names of any separation colour spaces in a PDF.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-print\-dict\-entry\f[R] \f[B]<key> in.pdf\f[R] [\-json]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-dict\-entry <key>\f[R] \f[B]in.pdf\f[R]
[\-dict\-entry\-search <term>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-replace\-dict\-entry <key> \-replace\-dict\-entry\-value
<value>\f[R] \f[B]in.pdf\f[R] [\-dict\-entry\-search <term>] \f[B]\-o
out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Low level operations to edit PDF objects directly.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for details.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-clipping in.pdf\f[R] [<range>] \f[B]\-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove any clipping paths from a PDF.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-obj[\-json] <object specification> in.pdf\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-replace\-obj <object specification>=<object> in.pdf \-o
out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-obj <object number> in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-extract\-stream[\-decompress] <object specification> in.pdf
\-o out.dat\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-replace\-stream <object specification>
\-replace\-stream\-with <filename> in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Low level operations to explore and edit PDF files object\-by\-object.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for details.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-contains\-javascript in.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Prints true if the PDF contains JavaScript, false otherwise.
.PP
\f[B]cpdf \-remove\-javascript in.pdf \-o out.pdf\f[R]
.PP
Remove JavaScript from a PDF.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]CPDF_SHOW_EXT\f[R]
Show command line of external commands as they are called if equal to
\(lqtrue\(rq.
.TP
\f[B]CPDF_DEBUG\f[R]
Same as adding \f[B]\-debug\f[R] to command line, if equal to
\(lqtrue\(rq.
.TP
\f[B]CPDF_REPRODUCIBLE_DATES\f[R]
Expand data \(lqnow\(rq to the same, false value each time, if equal to
\(lqtrue\(rq.
.TP
\f[B]CAMLPDF_REPRODUCIBLE_IDS\f[R]
Produce the same file ID each time, if equal to \(lqtrue\(rq.
